  "doc_id": "4780",
  "text": "Cigarette smoking is known to affect the airway microbiota 7 , but the extent and specificity of disruption shown here suggests an independent capacity to damage human health. The loss of diversity may predispose smokers to the recurrent infections that lead to COPD [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The annual rate of antibiotic prescription in the Australian population is 254 per 1000, and half of these will be for respiratory infections [CITATION_3] , so it is likely that many smokers will have intermittently been given antibiotics which will have contributed to the microbial community abnormalities.",
